    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a subclass containing around 650 species of segmented worms characterized by a small sucker, which contains the mouth at the anterior end of the body and a large sucker located at the posterior end, having a flattened body, and being aquatic or living on moist soil. A few species have been used by humans in clinical bloodletting for thousands of years.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
